Horse in beef products
Horse meat has been found in cans of beef products sold by two small British retailers at low prices, the Food Hygiene Agency said today.
Routine tests revealed that the products, made in January in Romania and sold by the chains Home Bargains and Quality Save, contained horse DNA in the amount of 1 to 5%.
