Bombardier earnings fall as deliveries and aircraft orders decline
Bombardier Inc, a Canadian aircraft and rail manufacturer, reported a 15 percent drop in net profit on Thursday, under pressure from lower orders and deliveries in the third quarter and contractual problems in its Trains division.
Montreal-based Bombardier also did not provide in-flight test data for its all-new CSeries aircraft or information on whether the aircraft will meet its ambitious commercial commissioning schedule before September.
