However, if no new orders are announced in the coming months, we expect the market to become more skeptical about the program.
Bombardier hopes the CSeries family of aircraft will be able to catapult it into the lower segment of a market now dominated by Boeing and Airbus.
The first test aircraft was unveiled in March and flew for the first time in September after months of delay.
But the number of firm orders for CSeries aircraft is modest to date at 177. It appears that potential buyers are waiting for the results of flight tests to validate the company's claims regarding the energy efficiency and potential for savings of the new airliner.
At present, the company has registered a total of 403 orders and purchase commitments from 15 customers and operators.
