I have gone through all the phases: misunderstanding, anger, pain, crying that starts on its own, anywhere, anytime, in unusual places, incongruous moments.
Then time eased the pain.
All that remained was the lack, this empty unresponsiveness, this need for her, to entrust me, to reassure me in the depths of her sweetness.
Yet she is there, silent presence, she is there and looks at me.
