Otherwise, we should imitate Norway and maintain our economic independence.
Scotland’s SNP government is – and should be noted – the most successful anti-austerity political movement in Europe, having won a dramatic majority in 2011 based on its opposition to the dark cuts proposed (and implemented) by Labour Chancellor Alistair Darling and the Conservative/Liberal Democrat coalition that followed.
